                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#6va"/>
                           <desc type="Record">Record concerning the gathering of the monks to prohibit the selling of the monastery’s books. The note, written in <ref target="#h1">Hand 1</ref>, has been partly corrected by
                              the same hand; six lines have been erased at the end.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ይቤሉ፡ መምህራን፡ ወኵሎሙ፡ ካህናት፡ ወሊቃውንት፡
                              ዘደብረ፡ ዳሞ፡ ተጋቢኦሙ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን። እስመ፡ ሰምዑ፡ ከመ፡ ሤጥዎን፡ ለብዙኃት፡ መጻሕፍት፡
                              ትካት፡ አብዳን፡ ሰብእ፡ አውሪዶሙ፡ እምደብር። ወበእንተዝ፡ ይቤሉ፡ አሠርነ፡ ወአውገዝነ፡ በቃልነ፡ ከመ፡
                              ኢትፃእ፡ ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ እምአንቀጸ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን። ወካዕበ፡ ይቤሉ፡ ለዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘሠረቃ፡ ወፈሐቃ፡
                              ወአውረዳ፡ እምደብር፡ ወአውፅአ፡ እምአንቀጸ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ለርእይ፡ ወአንብቦ፡ በውስቴታ፡
                              ይኩን፡ ውጉዘ፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ቃሎሙ፡ ለጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ አጋዕዝቲነ። ወበቃሉ፡ ለአረጋዊ፡ አቡነ፡ ወበቃለ፡
                              እግዝእትነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ ማርያም፡ እሙ፡ ለመድኃኒነ።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">
                              Gathered in the church, teachers and all priest and masters of Dabra Dāmmo said (the following) because
                              they heard that foolish men sold many old books having taken them down from the mountain. Because of this they said, ‘We condemn and
                              excommunicate with our word that this book may not leave the gate of the church’. And furthermore they said, ‘The one who stole this book
                              or erased (its text) or took it down from the mountain or brought it out from the gate of the church except for looking or reading inside
                              shall be excommunicated by the authority of the word of our lords Peter and Paul and by the word of our father ʾAragāwi and by the word
                              of our Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, mother of our Saviour’.</q>
                        </item>
